  subhead="You are fitting steel purlins in a dormer conversion at a four-bed detached in Botley — the steels are heavy, the crane operator is waiting for your signals, and your entire crew is focused on the lift. At 11am the homeowner three doors down texts: 'Hi — been watching your work going up. Looks really impressive. We have been thinking about a dormer on our house too. Can you come and look when you get a minute?' Your phone is in the van fifty metres away. Without AI SMS, the text waits until you clean up at 4pm. By then she has texted two other loft companies and one has already replied. With it, the AI responds at 11:01am, she confirms her address, and on Thursday morning you walk down the road with your laser measure."
  scenario="It is 9:20pm on a Tuesday. A homeowner in Summertown has just measured his loft for the third time — confirming 2.5 metres from floor joist to ridge, plenty of space for a dormer bedroom and en-suite. His wife agrees: it is time to start getting quotes. He texts three loft conversion companies: 'Hi — we have a 4-bed detached in OX2 with a big loft. Measured 2.5m at the ridge. Want a rear dormer to create a master suite — bedroom and en-suite. Do you do everything from design through to completion? Can you survey this week?' Without AI SMS, you see the text Wednesday morning. Two other specialists replied by 10pm Tuesday — one offered a Thursday survey, the other sent a portfolio link showing similar detached dormer conversions. Your Wednesday morning reply is third in the queue. With AI SMS, the response arrives at 9:21pm: 'Thank you for your message. Rear dormer conversions on detached houses are one of our most popular projects — 2.5 metres at the ridge provides excellent working height. Could you confirm whether you have any existing loft access and whether there are obstructions like tanks or chimney breasts? We will arrange a survey at your convenience.' He replies confirming a loft ladder, no tanks (moved to an airing cupboard), and a chimney breast on the east side. Wednesday morning you open the lead: 4-bed detached, OX2, rear dormer, master suite, 2.5m ridge height, loft ladder access, chimney breast east side, design-to-completion, survey requested. You call at 8am and book a Thursday evening survey."
